<doc id="321660" wikidata="Q841428" url="?curid=321660" title="Trojane">
<text>Trojane (; , ) is a settlement in the Municipality of Lukovica in central Slovenia. It lies in the northern part of the Sava Hills, on a hill near the border of two Slovene regions, Carniola and Styria. Until the freeway was finished in 2005, Trojane was on the main route from Ljubljana to Maribor.

==History==
The Romans built a road on the route connecting Aquileia, Emona, Atrans, and Celeia. Trojane was an important , military post, and marketplace, and the town was surrounded by a defensive wall.

The archaeological remains of Atrans can be still seen in Trojane. In the Roman Empire, Trojane (Atrans) was on the border between Italy and the province of Noricum.

==Popular culture==

Trojane is particularly known for the local restaurant&#x27;s jelly doughnuts (), originally made with apricot jam filling.
They also come in blueberry and chocolate flavour.

